    <item>
      <id>2</id>
      <text>The term applies also to metal derivatives of ammonia and amines, in which a cation replaces a hydrogen atom on nitrogen. Such compounds are also called azanides, e.g. [image: example azanide (lithium diisopropylamide)] lithium diisopropylamide, synonym lithium diisopropylazanide.</text>
